TERMS AND CONDITIONS
1. For Terms and Conditions please refer to Jetstream's "Public Charter Operator
Participant Contact" prior to booking your flight. Jetstream is the Charter Operator.
CANADA 3000 Airlines Limited is the air carrier.
2. Infants: Infants under 2 years travel free, but do not receive a seat nor any baggage
allowance (maximum 1 infant per adult). See Unaccompanied Minors #5.
3. Changes to Bookings: All tickets are non-refundable, non-transferable and are
applicable only for dates shown on coupons. If we change your departure or return by
more than 24 hours your alternatives are:
To accept the change as offered.
To accept an alternative flight at the applicable price.
To cancel your flight and obtain a full refund.
Unused air tickets are non-refundable and non-transferable.
Schedules shown in this flyer are correct as of the publishing date but are subject to
revision. Please confirm flight times and dates at time of booking. Passengers must
also reconfirm flight times 24 hours prior to departure using the telephone numbers
included in your ticket wallet.
4. Check-in: Sorry, advance seat selection is not available. Check-in opens 3 hours
prior to departure and closes 30 minutes prior to departure. You may not be allowed
to board, nor would you be entitled to a refund should you arrive after that time.
Please remember the airline reserves the right to deny boarding to any passenger they
deem intoxicated or in an unfit condition to fly.
5. Unaccompanied minors: 5 to 12 years of age who are travelling alone must have in
their possession the name, address and phone number of the responsible party at
embarkation and on arrival, and a completed Unaccompanied Minor form for each leg
of the journey (free of charge at the airport check-in). The escort must wait at the air-
port until the flight has departed.
6. Baggage Allowance: CANADA 3000 accepts 2 pieces of checked baggage with a
combined maximum weight of 20kgs (44 Ibs) per passenger on the aircraft. No bag-
gage allowance is provided for infants sharing a seat with their guardian. CANADA
3000 has limited facilities for baggage in excess of the above specified allowance
which is available at the rate of $5 per kilo. Hand baggage is strictly limited to one
piece per passenger not to exceed 26x38x51cms (10"x15" x20").
7. Documentation: It is the passengers' responsibility to ensure they have in their pos-
session proper citizenship identification for entry into Canada and the U.S.
Passengers without identification may be denied boarding. No refunds will be issued.
For reservations, contact:
JETSTREAM Travel
In St. Petersburg, Clearwater, Tampa, Dunedin
(813) 530-4675
All other areas in Florida
1-800-3000-765
2016.113.092.
